cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT 

This paper involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for procedural content generation (PCG) of levels for video games, specifically Super Mario Bros. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as GANs are a machine learning approach. The paper also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of fitness functions to optimize the generated levels, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
